rules.ruleString: (Must have passed 4 (I/W) units in {MED4000, MED4171, MED4182, MED4200} or  Must have passed 4 (I/W) units in {GMC4000, GMC4151, GMC4162, GMC4200} or  Must have passed 3 (I/W) units in {MED4000, MED4190, MED4200})
Any 3 (I/W) co-req units in {MED5092, MED5100, MED5102}
Must be enrolled in course version {4531, 4532, 4533, M6011, M6018, M6019}

description: MED5091 is focused on facilitating the transition of students into the medical workplace as beginning interns. Students will participate in a range of learning experiences which are designed to substantially enhance their clinical reasoning, diagnostic and case management skills. Students will participate in supervised clinical practice and related learning activities (learning modules). Furthermore, students will have the opportunity to broaden their knowledge and skills in self selected areas of clinical practice which may include electing a remote community, health or medicine related field.
faculty: Faculty of Medicine, Nursing and Health Sciences
